# Prettier Configuration Template

## Purpose

Opinionated code formatter for JavaScript, TypeScript, CSS, JSON, Markdown, and more. Enforces consistent style without debates.

## Official Documentation

- [Prettier Options](https://prettier.io/docs/en/options) - All configuration options
- [Configuration Files](https://prettier.io/docs/en/configuration) - Config file formats
- [Editor Integration](https://prettier.io/docs/en/editors) - IDE setup

## When to Use

- ✅ Any JavaScript/TypeScript project
- ✅ Projects wanting consistent formatting
- ✅ Teams wanting to avoid style debates

## When NOT to Use

- ❌ Projects using Biome (has built-in formatter)
- ❌ Projects where team strongly prefers manual formatting
- ❌ Non-code files only (use project-specific formatters)

## Required Marker Files

- `package.json`

## Trade-offs & Alternatives

| Alternative | When to Use Instead |
|-------------|---------------------|
| [Biome](https://biomejs.dev/) | Faster, all-in-one (lint + format) |
| [dprint](https://dprint.dev/) | Faster, more configurable |
| ESLint rules | When you need more control (not recommended) |

## Template

### JSON Format (.prettierrc)

```json
{
  "semi": true,
  "singleQuote": false,
  "tabWidth": 2,
  "useTabs": false,
  "trailingComma": "es5",
  "printWidth": 80,
  "bracketSpacing": true,
  "arrowParens": "always",
  "endOfLine": "lf"
}
```

### JavaScript Format (prettier.config.js)

```javascript
// prettier.config.js
/** @type {import("prettier").Config} */
const config = {
  semi: true,
  singleQuote: false,
  tabWidth: 2,
  useTabs: false,
  trailingComma: "es5",
  printWidth: 80,
  bracketSpacing: true,
  arrowParens: "always",
  endOfLine: "lf",

  // Override for specific files
  overrides: [
    {
      files: "*.md",
      options: {
        proseWrap: "always",
        printWidth: 100,
      },
    },
    {
      files: "*.json",
      options: {
        tabWidth: 2,
      },
    },
  ],
};

export default config;
```

### With Tailwind CSS Plugin

```javascript
// prettier.config.js
/** @type {import("prettier").Config} */
const config = {
  semi: true,
  singleQuote: false,
  tabWidth: 2,
  trailingComma: "es5",
  plugins: ["prettier-plugin-tailwindcss"],
  // Tailwind plugin options
  tailwindFunctions: ["clsx", "cn"],
};

export default config;
```

## Common Configuration Choices

### Semi-colons

```json
{
  "semi": true    // const x = 1;
  "semi": false   // const x = 1
}
```

### Quotes

```json
{
  "singleQuote": false,  // "string"
  "singleQuote": true,   // 'string'
  "jsxSingleQuote": false // JSX uses double regardless
}
```

### Trailing Commas

```json
{
  "trailingComma": "none",  // No trailing commas
  "trailingComma": "es5",   // Where valid in ES5 (objects, arrays)
  "trailingComma": "all"    // Everywhere (function params too)
}
```

### Print Width

```json
{
  "printWidth": 80,   // Classic terminal width
  "printWidth": 100,  // Modern screens
  "printWidth": 120   // Wide monitors
}
```

